title: Crude Oil Futures Edge Lower in Asian Trade
text: 0146 GMT [Dow Jones] Crude-oil futures edged lower in early Asian trade Monday in a shaky start to this weekâ€™s trading as investors keep a close watch on oil supply data. Oil is also pressured by underlying strength in the greenback, which posted gains last week on expectations of a Fed rate increase this year. U.S. jobs data at the end of this week will be in focus; markets in Hong Kong, South Korea and Taiwan are closed for a holiday today. ANZ Bank says CFTC reported speculative long positions in Nymex crude oil futures outnumbered short positions by last week, suggesting some positive build-up on bullish bets....
